Amazon Jobs Test Automation Project

This project contains automated tests for the Amazon Jobs website, built with JavaScript and Cypress. The project aims to validate key functionalities of the site, ensuring a smooth and user-friendly experience.
This repository is intended for anyone looking to automate test cases on the Amazon Jobs site using Cypress. To get started, make sure you have Node.js and Cypress installed.
__________________________________________________
Installation

Clone this repository to your local machine, and then install the dependencies:

git clone <repo-url>
cd <your-repo-directory>
npm install
__________________________________________________

Running the Tests

To run the tests, use the following commands:
Headless mode:
npx cypress run

Open Cypress test runner:
npx cypress open
From the Cypress test runner, select the test you want to execute.
